\
 the average amount collected by step is such that $$ A=\frac{a\mathbb E(N)+b-a}{\mathbb E(N)}=a+\frac{b-a}{\mathbb E(N)}. $$ One has $$ \mathbb E(N)=\sum_{k\geqslant1}\mathbb P(N\geqslant k)=\sum_{k\geqslant0}\prod_{i=1}^{k}(1-p(i)), $$ that is, in the present case, $$ \mathbb E(N)=\sum_{k=0}^{32}\prod_{i=1}^{k}\frac{98-3i}{100}. $$ Numerically, 
